  "content": "\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://shellsharks.social/@shellsharks\" class=\"u-url mention\"\u003e@\u003cspan\u003eshellsharks\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e I am surprised at the question because your site looks so automated!\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI think I passed over something that makes it more automated. In my template if a mastodon isn\u0026#39;t given in the front matter I actually loop over every mastodon post looking for the first post that includes a link to the current page so that it will automatically show on the correct blog post. This probably doesn\u0026#39;t scale but I can probably make something that updates the frontmatter with the exact mastodon post id. This happens at the top of this file:\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/sudorandom/sudorandom.dev/blob/main/layouts%2Fposts%2Fsingle.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" translate=\"no\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003ehttps://\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"ellipsis\"\u003egithub.com/sudorandom/sudorand\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003eom.dev/blob/main/layouts%2Fposts%2Fsingle.html\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eIf the builds get too long maybe I\u0026#39;ll write something that automatically does this once and adds the mastodon ID to the frontmatter but for now the build time is still pretty quick.\u003c/p\u003e",
